<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-462-356  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 462 356.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Iandamp;CS (Instrumentation andamp; Control Systems)  July 1989 v62 n7 p45(4).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>NIR analyzers earn their place in process control. (near infrared- includes related article on NIR success)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Bickel, Allen.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Advances in near infrared (NIR) technology have broadened itsapplications in measurement and control of petroleum, polymer,textile, chemical, and other material production processes.andP;  Thenewer more intelligent, easier-to-use, and more durable NIRspectrophotometers enable the faster and more precisedetermination of the constituents of tested samples through theanalysis of their NIR absorbance spectrum.andP;  Specific technologyadvancements that have improved NIR analysis performance includestronger enclosures for increased immunity to vibration for bettercalibration, advanced optical grating for both modeling andmeasurement with greater accuracy, powerful spectroscopicstatistical (chemometric) software, and multipoint fiber optics.andO;Each of these technologies are briefly described.andP;  NIR advantagesover other technologies are briefly discussed.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     Performance ImprovementAnalytical TechniquesMeasurement TechniquesChemistryHigh TechnologyFiber OpticsInfrared Technology.andO;Feature:   illustrationphotograph.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>